review_blob: I grow quite a bit of rye on the farm so I figured why not try rye beer. The smell is wonderful color just so tasty but there is vary little head. Fist sip is ok but there is a bitter sour after taste that doesnt work for me
Not much head out of any of the 6 bottles. Nice falvor with just the right hop bite. Price us not too bad for everynigh beer
Nice color and smell but the hops falvor is pretry sharp. A bit pricy for an every day type of beet
Nice malty brew but would like the knocked done just a touch. A bit pricy for an every day beer
beer_name: Three Floyds Robert The Bruce Scottish Ale
